Title: Ils découvrent les conditions de travail chez Action - Complément d’enquête
Description:
Retrouvez le reportage de Complément d'enquête, "Action: toujours moins cher mais à quel prix ?", en intégralité sur notre plateforme france.tv 👉 bit.ly/CDE-Action

Deux journalistes de Complément d'enquête se sont fait embaucher en CDI dans deux magasins de l'enseigne Action. Payés au SMIC, ils ont découvert le quotidien des salariés sous pression...

Avec près de 850 magasins en France, Action est devenu l'enseigne préférée des Français. En une décennie, le discounter néerlandais s'est imposé dans l'Hexagone. En cette période d'inflation, ses prix très serrés attirent toujours plus de clients. 

Complément d'enquête a découvert comment l'enseigne négocie avec ses fournisseurs pour obtenir les prix les plus bas possible, au détriment parfois de la qualité et de la sécurité des produits. De la réception des produits dans ses entrepôts à la mise en rayon en magasin, Action s'appuie sur une organisation millimétrée où chaque seconde compte. Le turnover dans certaines régions atteindrait un niveau très élevé, de 70% à 80%, et le nombre de maladies professionnelles et d'accidents du travail serait en augmentation.

TEST GADŻETÓW (chyba) Z ACTION
Description:
W tym odcinku Navcia odpakowuje ogromną paczkę gadżetów rożnego rodzaju :D!

A także Autopromocja - pokazuję jej swoje klawiaturki - macie mnie dość ^^?
► https://bit.ly/Onionite - Onionite, cebulka
► https://bit.ly/OnioniteWireless - bezprzewodowa, dostępna później
► https://bit.ly/DeltaZ - najlepsza pod customy
► https://bit.ly/GammaZ - wersja  magnetyczna

Navcia na Twitch:
► https://www.twitch.tv/navcia

Ktoś kto przygotowywał ten prezent pomyślał o tym, żeby był jak najbardziej uniwersalny. Ta osoba wsadziła wszelkiego rodzaju ciekawostki elektroniczne, które razem utworzyły ciekawą paczkę :D!

Mamy tutaj zarówno inteligentny głośnik Amazon Echo jako centralkę inteligentnego domu, zakładkę do książki z podświetleniem, czy miniaturową konsolkę retro do telewizora z dwoma padami :D

A to wszystko w serii AdwenTech, gdzie codziennie odpakowujemy nowe prezenty. Tym razem formuła odcinków jest nieco zmieniona - to Twórcy przygotowują paczki dla innych Twórców, a ja wykładam budżet ^^!

Finalnie w całej serii chodzi o to żeby się dobrze bawić. Spędzać miło czas i odkrywać to co w innych siedzi w głowach jak myślą o prezentach :D! AdwenTech to vlogmass. Kalendarz AdwenTech'owy. Miniaturowa seria, która przez 24 dni grudnia pozwala na znalezienie ciekawych inspiracji na prezent. Edycja Pomysł Na Prezent - kiedy nie wiesz jaki prezent kupić do konkretnej kwoty :D

W tym roku jest ciężko - bardzo ciężko :D! Już tyle różnych gadżetów mieliśmy na przestrzeni lat, że trzeba się nieźle postarać żeby znaleźć coś unikatowego. Czy naszym Twórcom się uda? Śledźcie serię i dawajcie znać w komentarzach co Wam się spodobało, a który prezent nie spełnił Waszych oczekiwań :D

Pozdro!

Balanced by gravity, righted by buoyancy. Witness science in action as we explore the fascinating physics behind boat stability! 🛥️

Title: How To Train Your Dragon | Official Teaser Trailer
Description:
How To Train Your Dragon - In Theaters June 13

From three-time Oscar® nominee and Golden Globe winner Dean DeBlois, the creative visionary behind DreamWorks Animation’s acclaimed How to Train Your Dragon trilogy, comes a stunning live-action reimagining of the film that launched the beloved franchise. 
On the rugged isle of Berk, where Vikings and dragons have been bitter enemies for generations, Hiccup (Mason Thames; The Black Phone, For All Mankind) stands apart. The inventive yet overlooked son of Chief Stoick the Vast (Gerard Butler, reprising his voice role from the animated franchise), Hiccup defies centuries of tradition when he befriends Toothless, a feared Night Fury dragon. Their unlikely bond reveals the true nature of dragons, challenging the very foundations of Viking society. 

With the fierce and ambitious Astrid (BAFTA nominee Nico Parker; Dumbo, The Last of Us) and the village’s quirky blacksmith Gobber (Nick Frost; Snow White and the Huntsman, Shaun of the Dead) by his side, Hiccup confronts a world torn by fear and misunderstanding. 
As an ancient threat emerges, endangering both Vikings and dragons, Hiccup’s friendship with Toothless becomes the key to forging a new future. Together, they must navigate the delicate path toward peace, soaring beyond the boundaries of their worlds and redefining what it means to be a hero and a leader. 

The film also stars Julian Dennison (Deadpool 2), Gabriel Howell (Bodies), Bronwyn James (Wicked), Harry Trevaldwyn (Smothered), Ruth Codd (The Midnight Club), BAFTA nominee Peter Serafinowicz (Guardians of the Galaxy) and Murray McArthur (Game of Thrones).
How to Train Your Dragon is written, produced and directed by DeBlois. It is also produced by three-time Oscar® nominee Marc Platt (Wicked, La La Land) and Emmy winner Adam Siegel (Drive, 2 Guns). How To Train Your Dragon is part of the Filmed For IMAX® Program, which offers filmmakers IMAX® technology to help them deliver the most immersive movie experience to audiences around the world. 

Inspired by Cressida Cowell’s New York Times bestselling book series, DreamWorks Animation’s How to Train Your Dragon franchise has captivated global audiences, earning four Academy Award® nominations and grossing more than $1.6 billion at the global box-office. Now, through cutting-edge visual effects, DeBlois transforms his beloved animated saga into a breathtaking live-action spectacle, bringing the epic adventures of Hiccup and Toothless to life with jaw-dropping realism as they discover the true meaning of friendship, courage and destiny.

"Riot for the Dove"

This is an exciting film that combines elements of action, science fiction and thriller. The plot revolves around a girl named Eliana, endowed with the unique ability to see remotely, a gift that allows her to observe events at a distance. She becomes the target of a dangerous cartel who kidnap her to use her powers for their criminal plans.

During her captivity, Eliana learns about the existence of a clock that has a unique property - the ability to jump seconds back in time. This device is an extremely valuable artifact that is hunted by both government agencies and criminal organizations. Sensing danger, Eliana uses her ability to find this watch, hoping it will be her only chance for salvation.

At this critical moment, a mysterious man appears on the scene, armed and determined, who has been sent to cross the border and rescue Eliana. This mysterious savior, a former operative with a troubled past, tries to bring her back to safety, but during the rescue operation they encounter unexpected difficulties. Eliana, realizing the importance of the watch, steals it, causing them both to flee.

Now the pair find themselves in the vortex of a dangerous game, pursued not only by a cartel bent on reclaiming the clock, but also by government agents who will stop at nothing to seize this powerful device. SEAL Team VI

This is a war film inspired by real events. The tape tells the heroic saga of the elite anti-terrorist SEAL team, which carries out a secret operation in Iraq four days before the start of Operation "Desert Storm". The task of the team is to carry out a top-secret mission to neutralize the enemy threat before a large-scale military offensive. The main characters are experienced and courageous soldiers who are ready to risk their lives for the safety of others. They carefully prepare for the task, taking into account all possible risks and dangers. The team commander leads his soldiers through harsh conditions and hostile territory hoping for mission success. However, when their covert operation is compromised, the team faces unpredictable and deadly consequences. The enemy is aware of their presence, and now the heroes must fight for their survival in an environment where every mistake can cost them their lives. They fall into traps, suffer losses, and face challenges that test their courage, endurance, and teamwork.

The film not only depicts combat actions and military strategies, but also delves into the inner world of the heroes. The film shows how they cope with psychological pressure, fear and loss, leaving on the screen touching scenes of friendship, self-sacrifice and dedication to their work. This tape conveys the spirit of courage and self-sacrifice inherent in elite military units. The director creates a tense atmosphere that keeps the viewer in constant tension, and the battle scenes impress with their realism and dynamics. The inspiration behind this video:

Tom Holland has long been considered a top contender to portray Ben Tennyson in a live-action adaptation, with fan-made concept trailers championing him for the role. Among the various Ben 10 storylines, Alien Force seems to be the best fit for Holland. In some ways, Ben Tennyson shares similarities with Peter Parker. Both characters are young heroes burdened with the responsibility of saving the world from dangerous villains, making the role somewhat familiar territory for Holland. Following the success of Spider-Man: Homecoming, where Holland was praised for capturing the complexities of a young hero with overwhelming responsibilities, he’s proven he can thrive in this type of role. However, Ben 10: Alien Force has a much darker tone. With its more intricate plot, fewer comedic moments, and the willingness to kill off characters, it marks a shift from the lighter, more heroic portrayals Holland has been known for thus far.

Although he’s set to lead several major films, including Uncharted, Holland has shown a growing interest in grittier narratives, as seen in projects like The Devil All the Time and Cherry. A Ben 10: Alien Force adaptation could serve as the perfect blend of the lighter superhero roles he's excelled in and the darker, more complex characters he’s eager to explore. The franchise comes with a built-in fanbase, and the source material was considered challenging and sophisticated when it first aired. While plans for a live-action adaptation currently seem dormant, should they move forward, Holland would be an excellent choice to lead the project.
